        "header": "3Scaling Laws of Learning from Real World Environments",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2607.05155/2607.05155v1/x22.png",
                "caption": "Figure 5:Task-family-level log-sigmoid fits across the six EdgeBench task families.\nDespite large differences in task type and scoring function, the same\nlog-time sigmoidal form fits the average trajectory in each task family well.111Fit precision improves as the number of fitted tasks increases; see\nFigure8.",
                "position": 587
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2607.05155/2607.05155v1/x23.png",
                "caption": "Figure 6:Long-horizon log-sigmoid fits beyond the main 12-hour benchmark window.\nThe left panel fits 28-hour trajectories averaged over 80 tasks; the right panel fits\n72-hour trajectories averaged over 18 tasks. All fitted curves remain highly precise,\nwithR2≥0.993R^{2}\\geq 0.993.",
                "position": 594
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2607.05155/2607.05155v1/x23.png",
                "caption": "Figure 6:Long-horizon log-sigmoid fits beyond the main 12-hour benchmark window.\nThe left panel fits 28-hour trajectories averaged over 80 tasks; the right panel fits\n72-hour trajectories averaged over 18 tasks. All fitted curves remain highly precise,\nwithR2≥0.993R^{2}\\geq 0.993.",
                "position": 597
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2607.05155/2607.05155v1/x24.png",
                "caption": "Figure 7:Forecasting 12-hour performance from the first 6.5 hours. Log-sigmoid\nfits on this early window accurately predict the held-out remainder for all five\nmodels.222GPT-5.4 service availability dropped in the latter half of the\nexperiment, which may partly explain its forecast deviation; see\nAppendix9.",
